ce": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/i/status/2073456032588984506", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "McDonald\u2019s locations are having to take drastic measures to ensure the safety of their workers\r\n\r\nNew barriers are being put up over ordering counters to stop confrontations and angry customers from climbing over to fight employees", "last_comment_created": 1783212610388, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 11, "score_up": 34, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 154, "created": 1783185415000, "id": "2073456032588984506", "video": {"preview": "https://pbs.twimg.com/amplify_video_thumb/2073455945854881793/img/YaQISNTfpDkJU1fR.jpg", "mpeg": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2073455945854881793/pl/7nUjdGm-hrRj3ZgX.m3u8?v=46f", "aspectRatio": [9, 16], "heightRatio": 177, "type": "video/mp4", "url": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2073455945854881793/vid/avc1/320x568/1yEBxa5wtEC4WBVH.mp4"}, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1593753619148382208/YYzzCs6C_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Wall Street Apes", "username": "WallStreetApes"}, "content": "McDonald\u2019s locations are having to take drastic measures to ensure the safety of their workers\n\nNew barriers are being put up over ordering counters to stop confrontations and angry customers from climbing over to fight employees\n\nThis is only being done at locations where crime", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 1150}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ATBlwJ6i9", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 21, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "god", "id": 8713931, "raw_content": "Happy 250th Independence Day America! Cheering for you guys from the Philippines!\n\nIt's interesting how, as I learn more about history, I realize just how much my country owes to America. Despite more than three centuries of Spanish rule, and even with most of our names (and most likely a good percentage of our genetics) deriving from Spain, I can say for certain that America now has a much greater influence on our country today, even from less than half a century of having been occupied by the US.\n\nMy own country's history - or at least the narrative that's regularly taught to us here - is based around a revolutionary spirit against Spain that is more than likely a bizarre copy of the truth behind America's repudiation of the British. It's funny how I learned recently that the Spanish-American War that freed us from Spain was more likely instigated by journalists waging a propaganda war, escalating all the way to the Treaty of Paris that gave us over to the US.\n\nMy country regards July 4 as Philippine-American Friendship Day because our actual independence was signed on July 4, 1946 when the US gave the Philippines its freedom to self-govern. To this day, after almost 400 years of being a colony, my country is still struggling to understand what it means to be independent.\n\nWhatever the true story is, I am inspired whenever I look at America and see what it really means to declare independence and fight to defend one's freedom. And it is nothing short of God's divine providence that has kept America free for its 250 years. I pray that America finds its way back to the ideals that freed them from an oppressive crown and let freedom ring all over the world.\n\nHappy 250th Birthday! May God bless the United States of America!", "author": "upside-downPHflag", "created": 1783216046398, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Happy 250th America! (and Happy Philippine-American Friendship Day!)", "last_comment_created": 1783216046398, "content": "<p>Happy 250th Independence Day America! Cheering for you guys from the Philippines!</p>\n<p>It's interesting how, as I learn more about history, I realize just how much my country owes to America. Despite more than three centuries of Spanish rule, and even with most of our names (and most likely a good percentage of our genetics) deriving from Spain, I can say for certain that America now has a much greater influence on our country today, even from less than half a century of having been occupied by the US.</p>\n<p>My own country's history - or at least the narrative that's regularly taught to us here - is based around a revolutionary spirit against Spain that is more than likely a bizarre copy of the truth behind America's repudiation of the British. It's funny how I learned recently that the Spanish-American War that freed us from Spain was more likely instigated by journalists waging a propaganda war, escalating all the way to the Treaty of Paris that gave us over to the US.</p>\n<p>My country regards July 4 as Philippine-American Friendship Day because our actual independence was signed on July 4, 1946 when the US gave the Philippines its freedom to self-govern. To this day, after almost 400 years of being a colony, my country is still struggling to understand what it means to be independent.</p>\n<p>Whatever the true story is, I am inspired whenever I look at America and see what it really means to declare independence and fight to defend one's freedom. And it is nothing short of God's divine providence that has kept America free for its 250 years. I pray that America finds its way back to the ideals that freed them from an oppressive crown and let freedom ring all over the world.</p>\n<p>Happy 250th Birthday! May God bless the United States of America!</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 0, "score_up": 21, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "\u271d\ufe0f\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0UNDER GOD\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u271d\ufe0f", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ATBlwIq3v", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 23, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8713893, "raw_content": "", "author": "MagaJay02", "created": 1783214199486, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "MagaJay02", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "rumble.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ATBlwIq3v.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://rumble.com/shorts/v7c9n2s", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "This was the line getting into the Great American State Fair earlier! 2+ hours! ", "last_comment_created": 1783214238994, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 1, "score_up": 23, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"description": "", "large_image": "T2BP3dTN9fIr1PI3.png", "title": "22 seconds of the line going into Great American State Fair July 4th"}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_commen